                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17450424-12-off65 t17450424-12-crimeloc67"></join> . I was called up by these two neighbours, on the 4th of March at twelve o'clock at night, and they had got the prisoner lying upon his back in the yard. There were seven hens killed, one cock, and four ducks; they were lying in a bag a little way from the road. The prisoner said he would have killed them all, if he had not been disturbed; he said there was another with him, and owned he held the bag while the fowls were killing.</p>
