            . My wife saw two men go by, and each of them had a bag; she told me of it: I got up and followed them with a gun. I called my neighbour Paulin up to go with me. I saw the prisoner and another man come out of Mr. Smith's hen-house. I took hold of the prisoner with one hand, and had my gun in the other. He pulled at it several times, but could not get it out of my hand. One got away, and I threw the prisoner upon his back in the snow. He is a lamp lighter; he said he was trimming of lamps at eight o'clock that night in Smithfield .</p>
